@psbanka Revisiting this... it doesn't seem like authenticating by password is supported by Fastly's API anymore. In the `auth.py` file there's a call to the `/login` endpoint: https://github.com/fastly/fastly-py/blob/master/fastly/auth.py#L18

but in the API docs I cannot find any mention of a `/login` endpoint: https://docs.fastly.com/api/auth

The reason I removed these 3 tests is because I thought Fastly deprecated username+password authentication in favor of Key-based authentication. Is this not the case?

